commit.message: Merge branch 'jwt27-debian'

Avoid problems when creating the debug package

- The makefile needs explicit definition of the prefix
Merge branch 'debian' of https://github.com/jwt27/tvision into jwt27-debian

Revert changes to makes/common.imk

- The RHIDE_LD_FLAGS var can't be used for regular linking
bump debhelper compat version to 7
Add -Werror back to RHIDE_OS_BOTH_LINUX.  We addressed all the warnings that caused the build to fail.

Make TDisplayWinGr::className const char * to avoid warning about conversion from string constant to non-const pointer.

In TDisplayWinGr::SetFontCrt, add CLY_Unused modifier to fontObject to avoid warning about unused variable.

In TDisplayWinGr::processEvent, fix formatting to avoid warning about misleading indentation.
Merge branch 'set-soft:master' into develop

commit.message:
New compatlayer definition CLY_Unused

- Fixes regex.c issues when using -Werror

Enable specification of LDFLAGs during configure. The motivation for these changes is to enable building of 32-bit binaries on a 64-bit platform.  configure already enabled passing -m32 to both CFLAGS And CXXFLAGS, but was missing LDFLAGS.  With that, you could only compile, but not link.
Changes to enable Microsoft compiler to build.

Incorporated most changes from Pull Request #4

Some remain to be reviewed.

Merge branch 'guy-rouillier-develop'
Reverted svrapi.h unconditional change, we must change it only when needed
Reverted pid_t change to unsigned
Removed tabs and avoided moving CLY_ssize_t outside its scope
Reverted space changes
Reverted space changes and added a comment about compatlayer.h

Add svrapi.h, which is no longer included in Windows toolkits.  Included the version from MinGW-w64, which has no copyright. The only file including this header is compat/unc_95.c; compilers affected include MSVC, Borland and Watcom on the Windows platform.

Minor changes resulting from review of pull request #4. One significant change is in compatlayer.h. For TVCompf_MingGW, moved inclusion of _ming.h and sys/types.h to the top of that section.  We need that in order to test for _SSIZE_T_DEFINED when setting Uses_CLY_ssize_t
Minor changes for compatibility with Mingw-w64 in Windows 64-bit.  Tested generating both 64-bit and 32-bit executables.

Fixed missing strcpy declaration in i18n example.
Fixes #2
Changed maintainance debug format from stabs+3 to gdb3
Made ar command configurable.
Adjusted (c) years

Added configuration option to exclude libgpm

- Fixes #1

Added `ar` command now can be configured from the environment

- Using the AR environment variable.
- Related to issue: #1
- Gentoo issue: https://bugs.gentoo.org/796278
Updated the change.log
Added deb and deb_clean as main Makefile targets.
Made debian/rules executable.
Updated the change.log with the last 13 commits.
